<div id="review_302119173" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/302119173" />
    <a title="Preeti Joan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4796514-preeti-joan"><img alt="Preeti Joan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1409728442p2/4796514.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/302119173?book_show_action=true">Mar 27, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Preeti Joan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Preeti Joan" href="/user/show/4796514-preeti-joan">Preeti Joan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer302119173" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13241106496094891592"><s>Sorry but I&apos;m didn&apos;t find this book amazing, at all. It is such a let-down. I&apos;m disappointed. :(<br/><br/>I&apos;ll explain later. :) Longer review coming up!</s><br/><br/><br/>Like I said earlier in my temporary review, I was expecting a <u>LOT</u> from this sequel. It turns out that the book didn&apos;t not meet them. So here I am sitting outside our house having my <b>pity party</b>. Why&apos;s that? Here are a few things why:<br/><br/><br/>1st: The events are repetitive. I&apos;ve gone tired reading over and over again how they fought with the enemies and having Gabi </span>
  <span id="freeText13241106496094891592" style="display:none"><s>Sorry but I'm didn't find this book amazing, at all. It is such a let-down. I'm disappointed. :(<br /><br />I'll explain later. :) Longer review coming up!</s><br /><br /><br />Like I said earlier in my temporary review, I was expecting a <u>LOT</u> from this sequel. It turns out that the book didn't not meet them. So here I am sitting outside our house having my <b>pity party</b>. Why's that? Here are a few things why:<br /><br /><br />1st: The events are repetitive. I've gone tired reading over and over again how they fought with the enemies and having Gabi injured and, again, saved by Marcello. When I predict something that might come to that event, I said <i>"Here we go again!"</i>.<br /><br /><br />2nd: So many <i>touchy-feely</i> scenes! Goodness gracious! Can't they wait 'till they win the war then have their own moments?! Please! I really thought that this book was not one of those with cheesy love scenes! <br /><br />3rd: The events were not what I had in mind! It left me hanging! And the decisions the characters made were <i>swift</i> and <i>careless</i>.<br /><br /><br />So yeah! Good thing I'm generous enough not to give this book 1 or 2 stars. Instead, I gave it <b>3 stars</b>! :)) I'm not setting a high standard for the next book, so it better be good! :D</span>
  <a data-text-id="13241106496094891592" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
